result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of both charges. Because Wisconsin law provides for only one penalty even if there is a conviction on both, no additional penalty has been imposed as a result of the second charge.

  • Laura L Hunt was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Laura L Hunt was found guilty of Operating w/ PAC (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

State rests its case in chief. 1:36 pm Jury excused. 1:37 pm Motion for directed verdict by Attorney Johnson-Court denies motion for directed verdict or dismissal. Court questions defendant regarding the defendant's 5th and 6th amendment rights and accepts defendant's right to not testify. 1:58 pm jury returns to the courtroom. 2:25 pm Instruction conference. 2:37 pm case recalled-jury returned to the courtroom. Court instructs jury. Closing statement by DA Blader. Closing statment by Attorney Johnson. Bailiff's charged. Jury begins deliberation at 3:34 pm. 4:02 pm case recalled-same appearances. Court has received a note from the jury-verdict reached. Guilty on Count 1 & Guilty on Count 2. Court polls individual juror-verdict represents verdicts of juror and jury as a whole. Motion by DA Blader for judgment on verdicts. Attorney Johnson makes motion . Court enters judgment on the verdicts as found by the jury. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Johnson. Statement by Defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: 45 days WCJ with Huber and Good Time Credit. Credit for 1 day served. To commence immediatley. 48 hour rule explained. AODA and follow through to include IOP, Absolute Sobriety, not be on the premises of any bars, defendant is not to possess nor ingest any impairing substance.  $2,500.00 fine inclusive of costs plus $42.50 blood draw fee & Attorney Johnson's fees,  30 month DL revocation, 30 month IID, OWI Assessment.
